summary: VEHICLE WOULD NOT START. ALL LIGHTS WORKED, BUT NOTHING ELSE. IT COULD NOT BE TAKEN OUT OF PARK. TOW TRUCK DRIVER TRIED TO JUMP START, BUT BATTERY WAS GOOD. HE HAD TO DRAG THE  FWD VEHICLE INTO A POSITION WHERE HE COULD TOW IT FROM THE FRONT.   DEALER SAID CAUSE WAS THE WIN MODULE (OVER $300 AND IT IS OUT OF WARRANTY). THERE COULD BE MORE ISSUES BUT THEY WILL NOT KNOW UNTIL PART ARRIVES.  THERE APPEAR TO BE MANY ISSUES WITH THIS PART ON THIS AND OTHER DODGE VEHICLES, BUT NO RECOGNITION OF A SAFETY ISSUE.  *TR
